<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fully-adv">fully <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fʊli/    美 /'fʊli/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-completely">1.★ <strong>完全地；充分地；彻底地 (completely)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>fully understand</strong> why you are not comfortable about it.
我完全理解你为何对此事感到不舒服。</p><footer>2009 安徽书面表达改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If we prepare fully, we can achieve great things.
做好充分的准备我们就能取得好成绩。</p><footer>译林⑤ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>足足；至少：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There were fully 200 people present at the ceremony.
足足有200人出席典礼。</p></div></div>